1
00:00:27,839 --> 00:00:29,559
What are you doing, Ido?

2
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:32,479
Spelling "Nazli".
It's the name of my beloved.

3
00:00:38,359 --> 00:00:39,359
Boys!

4
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:44,000
The teacher is coming.
Put it back in your pants.

5
00:00:44,119 --> 00:00:45,960
I haven't finished spelling it.

6
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:49,759
What's going on? Come here.

7
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,131
How many times do I have to tell you
not to come here?

8
00:00:54,195 --> 00:00:55,682
This place is dangerous, but here you are.

9
00:00:55,881 --> 00:00:57,119
But we've never fallen.

10
00:01:01,280 --> 00:01:02,920
And they wrote a "U" here.

11
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:05,079
It's not a "U", it's an "N".

12
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:07,200
The first letter in his beloved's name.

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,920
Go on, we're leaving.
I'll take you to your homes.

14
00:01:12,799 --> 00:01:16,000
How many times do I have to tell you?
This place is dangerous.

15
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:18,840
Do you know what would happen
if you fell from there?

16
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:20,760
You'd be gone.

17
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:23,400
I'll tell your mother about this.

18
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:45,840
Zeyno!

19
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,719
Yes, Dad?

20
00:01:52,599 --> 00:01:54,760
I've given your hand in marriage
to your cousin Kasim.

21
00:01:57,319 --> 00:01:58,519
Idiot.

22
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,079
Idiot!

23
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,319
They're taking you away tomorrow.

24
00:02:03,519 --> 00:02:05,359
Dad, he is like a brother to me.

25
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,400
For heaven's sake!

26
00:02:08,199 --> 00:02:10,719
Look, I'm your father. You'll do as I say.

27
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:13,719
Go on. Go back home!

28
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:23,039
Roll the dice.

29
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:26,400
-It's not your turn to play.
-It's not?

30
00:02:38,439 --> 00:02:40,479
Good God!

31
00:02:41,879 --> 00:02:43,280
Shit!

32
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:46,759
Let's see what your mothers think.

33
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,400
What have you done?

34
00:02:55,639 --> 00:02:57,639
Not much. I'm just chilling.
What have you done?

35
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,680
The boys were near the cliffs, again.

36
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:05,360
Damn it!
Didn't I tell you not to go there?

37
00:03:05,479 --> 00:03:08,319
Why did you do that?
Your clothes are covered in dirt again!

38
00:03:08,719 --> 00:03:10,719
Do I look like a washing machine to you?

39
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:12,840
Sister Kibar.

40
00:03:14,159 --> 00:03:17,919
Seriously, that place is really dangerous.
Please be careful.

41
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:19,199
Dangerous?

42
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,000
These kids don't care
about danger, Teacher.

43
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:24,919
It took three delivery nurses
to deliver this one.

44
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:26,719
See, he is still in one piece.

45
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,599
What's going on, sister?

46
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,800
These brats of yours
went to the cliffs again.

47
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,960
-Oh?
-Yes, I caught them.

48
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:35,560
-It's so dangerous.
-Dangerous?

49
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:37,120
These kids don't care about danger.

50
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:39,759
Hey! Do I look like
a washing machine to you?

51
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:41,400
Okay, that's enough.

52
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,599
There will be a meeting
at the school today.

53
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,719
-Okay, I'll bring the second wife with me.
-Sister…

54
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:50,520
-"Second wife" is politically incorrect.
-So what?

55
00:03:50,719 --> 00:03:53,240
-Say "partner". It's more polite.
-Please.

56
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:56,879
Have a good day.

57
00:03:58,759 --> 00:04:00,800
-Get in!
-Go on! Get in there!

58
00:04:07,599 --> 00:04:08,639
Come on!

59
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,919
Here we are.

60
00:04:14,759 --> 00:04:16,519
You said it'd be closer to the village.

61
00:04:16,879 --> 00:04:18,879
The village is just beyond that hill.

62
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,279
Is there a bridge?
How am I supposed to get across?

63
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:24,480
-There is a bridge.
-But it's collapsed.

64
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,720
That's true.

65
00:04:26,839 --> 00:04:31,759
When they built the bridge, they said
it would bring freedom, peace, and unity.

66
00:04:32,399 --> 00:04:34,399
-But that didn't happen.
-What are you on about?

67
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:36,240
How am I supposed to get across?

68
00:04:36,759 --> 00:04:40,040
Go back to the town,
find someone with a car and come back.

69
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:41,199
Come back?

70
00:04:41,279 --> 00:04:43,439
-Are you messing with me?
-I'm just kidding.

71
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:47,399
I'll deliver my cargo
and then I'll take you to Teacher Salih.

72
00:04:50,279 --> 00:04:51,279
Come on!

73
00:04:54,319 --> 00:04:57,160
If you're going to try
to educate us again, I don't want to.

74
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:00,839
What's the point of teaching us
to read and write?

75
00:05:00,959 --> 00:05:03,439
No, it's not about that.
Take a seat and we'll begin.

76
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,800
-No, they're fine.
-We barely have enough room here.

77
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:09,439
-I'm talking to the women, Brother Zulfo.
-So?

78
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:12,560
Don't tire yourself out, Teacher. Really.

79
00:05:12,639 --> 00:05:14,759
We're used to it.
You'll get used to it too.

80
00:05:15,439 --> 00:05:18,519
-When will we get our food supplies?
-What are you doing here, Chief?

81
00:05:18,839 --> 00:05:20,920
You don't have any kids.
Who told you to come?

82
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:30,560
The classroom belongs to the state.
It's not your property.

83
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:34,319
What is in the box, Teacher?

84
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:38,199
We've received some shoes for the kids,
thanks to the city.

85
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:40,560
-What do the kids need shoes for?
-What about us?

86
00:05:46,399 --> 00:05:49,800
-These won't fit me.
-They're for the kids. Just sit down!

87
00:05:54,519 --> 00:05:57,079
At the beginning of the year,
I called you all for a meeting,

88
00:05:57,199 --> 00:05:58,480
but none of you came.

89
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,040
So I had to lie about the supplies.
I'm sorry about that.

90
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:05,319
Don't apologize, Teacher.
They're too dumb to get it.

91
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,439
There are some problems with the kids.

92
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:09,319
Idris, for example.

93
00:06:09,439 --> 00:06:12,639
You always talk about their kids.
Talk a little bit about mine too.

94
00:06:12,959 --> 00:06:14,240
Your kid is smart.

95
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:17,920
He is just having trouble focusing.

96
00:06:18,399 --> 00:06:19,800
How come?

97
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:24,480
-How many kids do you have?
-How many kids do I have?

98
00:06:27,759 --> 00:06:31,000
To keep a long story short,
the kids are all lagging behind.

99
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:33,279
Well, do something about it then.

100
00:06:33,519 --> 00:06:35,959
Mine probably takes after his mom.
Her family isn't very bright.

101
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:37,839
Well, he is my uncle's son.

102
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,360
Right, and there is that issue.

103
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,560
Marriages within the same families
are problematic. We need to talk about it.

104
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:47,319
It's really problematic.
You can't beat them, can't curse at them!

105
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,319
They're relatives after all.

106
00:06:53,399 --> 00:06:54,879
Does anyone have a shoehorn?

107
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:59,759
-There is the bell.
-Get up.

108
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,759
-Let's go.
-Where are you going?

109
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,920
Fits like a glove.

110
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:19,199
Well, Teacher, I…

111
00:07:20,519 --> 00:07:23,199
Well, let me take these and…

112
00:07:24,079 --> 00:07:27,279
give them to needy people in the village.

113
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,079
Go ahead, Chief.

114
00:07:36,879 --> 00:07:38,800
I'd just take them back anyway.

115
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,959
-Chief?
-Yes?

116
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:50,959
Where are you taking the shoes?

117
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:53,079
-They're for the kids!
-Well…

118
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:56,279
You see, these shoes
are designed for city streets.

119
00:07:56,439 --> 00:07:59,399
It's so rocky here.
It would be a shame to waste these shoes.

120
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,600
You know?

121
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:30,879
"The man said, 'Some love stories
aren't meant to be finished.'"

122
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:33,639
"'It wasn't likely to happen,
and it didn't,' replied the woman."

123
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:37,480
"It was a complete disappointment."

124
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:41,840
"And then they caught each other's eye,
possibly for the last time."

125
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,000
OATH OF LOVE

126
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,399
-What's wrong?
-So did they break up?

127
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,759
It's just a story, Zeynep.

128
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,840
What if our story ends like that?

129
00:08:57,519 --> 00:08:58,519
Our story?

130
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,279
Don't we have a story?

131
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:04,080
Yes. Of course we have a story.

132
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:09,080
We've had a story since the day you came
and took a book from me.

133
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:26,559
Zeynep?

134
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,080
OATH OF LOVE

135
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,759
-Have you finished it?
-I have not.

136
00:09:36,759 --> 00:09:39,679
Why? You seemed to enjoy it
when I was reading it to you.

137
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,639
I believed it when you were reading it,
but it isn't real.

138
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:48,159
Don't give me any more books, Teacher.

139
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,759
Why?

140
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,080
Because then I'll believe.

141
00:09:58,919 --> 00:10:02,360
Then I'll believe that love exists
and I'll start to dream.

142
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,799
Love does exist.

143
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:09,799
Not for me.
There is only pain for me.

144
00:10:11,759 --> 00:10:13,440
My dad has given me to Kasim.

145
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,200
My cousin.

146
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,200
But what about us?

147
00:10:24,639 --> 00:10:25,759
There is no us.

148
00:10:32,919 --> 00:10:35,240
Goodbye, Teacher Salih.

149
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,519
Goodbye.

150
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:47,559
Goodbye?

151
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,840
What do I do now?

152
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,720
FROM SALIH OZTURK
TO THE MINISTRY OF FAMILY, ANKARA

153
00:11:15,799 --> 00:11:18,600
"To the Republic of Turkey's
Ministry of Family,

154
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:22,440
I've been working as a teacher
in the village of Elaldi for three years."

155
00:11:22,879 --> 00:11:25,720
"This is the 38th letter
I have sent to the ministry."

156
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:32,559
"I have reported what happened
in the village after the collapse

157
00:11:32,679 --> 00:11:34,720
of the Freedom and Equality Bridge."

158
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:40,639
"The people here are so cut off
from the outside world."

159
00:11:41,919 --> 00:11:43,559
"Since the bridge's collapse,

160
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:46,960
the villagers have resorted to
marrying their cousins."

161
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,960
"And these types of marriages
cause problems,

162
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,720
not just for the families,
but also for the kids."

163
00:11:55,799 --> 00:11:59,240
"I would like the Ministry
to do something about this."

164
00:11:59,759 --> 00:12:02,360
"I kindly request
that you take the necessary action."

165
00:12:02,519 --> 00:12:04,120
"Teacher Salih Ozturk."

166
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,159
Hello, Chief.

167
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:12,240
Oh, hi. How can I help you?

168
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:17,120
Is this the food from the supply boxes?

169
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:20,120
No, it's not.

170
00:12:21,039 --> 00:12:23,120
I swear to God, I gave them to the poor.

171
00:12:24,279 --> 00:12:27,440
-Can you please send this letter ASAP?
-Oh, another letter.

172
00:12:27,679 --> 00:12:29,000
Of course.

173
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,600
Let me see if it smells nice.

174
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,679
Teacher, you know…

175
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:39,919
you keep writing these letters
to your beloved…

176
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:46,440
but she never responds, does she?

177
00:12:47,159 --> 00:12:48,440
Just accept it.

178
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,200
She doesn't love you back.

179
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:54,960
She does not.

180
00:13:02,559 --> 00:13:05,360
ELALDI VILLAGE
MARKET

181
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:08,440
It's not a girl, it's the state.
And it dislikes us, not just me.

182
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:13,360
DOSTLAR CAFE

183
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,080
See, there's the teacher.

184
00:15:17,159 --> 00:15:19,360
The one sitting over there,
with a gloomy face.

185
00:15:27,879 --> 00:15:28,879
Go!

186
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:35,320
-Salih Ozturk?
-Yes, that's me.

187
00:15:35,679 --> 00:15:38,559
I came from Ankara.
I'm from the Ministry. We need to talk.

188
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,720
Welcome.

189
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,799
Please, have a seat.

190
00:15:49,559 --> 00:15:52,559
Brother Hasan, we have a guest
from Ankara. Get us some tea.

191
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,360
There is no tea.

192
00:15:59,639 --> 00:16:02,840
-He said "Ankara".
-Let's go before something bad happens.

193
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:05,320
You already know what it's about.

194
00:16:06,559 --> 00:16:08,399
You wrote 37 letters.

195
00:16:08,519 --> 00:16:10,679
-Yes, I did.
-Bravo.

196
00:16:11,799 --> 00:16:14,679
The Ministry of Family has been working
on a project for years

197
00:16:15,639 --> 00:16:17,440
to strengthen family values.

198
00:16:17,519 --> 00:16:20,000
To increase the number
of official marriages.

199
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,200
To solve domestic issues
involving wives and children.

200
00:16:22,279 --> 00:16:24,240
To stop consanguineous marriages.

201
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:27,720
If the project is successful,
we'll apply it on a national level.

202
00:16:28,039 --> 00:16:29,360
That is the project.

203
00:16:29,799 --> 00:16:31,440
Would the villagers accept it?

204
00:17:01,360 --> 00:17:05,000
Villagers! A man from Ankara
has set foot in Elaldi Village,

205
00:17:05,599 --> 00:17:09,200
and he has something important
to tell all of you.

206
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:12,920
So, everyone, please gather
at the village square.

207
00:17:16,680 --> 00:17:18,799
-Someone from Ankara is here.
-Damn!

208
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:21,240
From Ankara? Who is he?

209
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,480
How'd he get here?
Did you see him? Who told you?

210
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,720
Just go away.

211
00:17:24,799 --> 00:17:27,079
-Help the kids get dressed.
-Which kids?

212
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,759
Yours or mine?

213
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:32,160
Well, my kids are so little.
I'll help them get dressed.

214
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,720
Don't look at me like that.

215
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:38,640
You said it'd be nice
to bring your cousin in.

216
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,039
What can I do?

217
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:45,039
I thought she would help with the chores,
but she is so dumb. Your mom was right.

218
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:48,160
She foresaw all this.

219
00:17:49,119 --> 00:17:52,559
-I heard everything.
-So? Help the kids get dressed.

220
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,440
Where is my pink turban?

221
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,200
We have a guest from Ankara.
I should look elegant.

222
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:01,640
It's not about you.
The men will take care of it.

223
00:18:01,839 --> 00:18:05,000
-I should go and see what it's about.
-I have to see it too.

224
00:18:05,279 --> 00:18:06,960
I'll kill myself to see him if necessary.

225
00:18:27,839 --> 00:18:29,480
Why is an official from Ankara here?

226
00:18:29,839 --> 00:18:31,480
We probably messed up big time.

227
00:18:31,720 --> 00:18:33,720
-What will he say?
-Well, it's obvious.

228
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,119
"Don't do it again,"
or something like that.

229
00:18:46,519 --> 00:18:47,960
Do you see any women here?

230
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,279
Hello, boys.

231
00:18:52,079 --> 00:18:53,839
Good God…

232
00:18:56,799 --> 00:18:57,960
Come on, Zulfo.

233
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,759
-Hello.
-What's going on?

234
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:02,440
-Hi.
-Hi.

235
00:19:04,039 --> 00:19:06,480
-He came from Ankara?
-What is this about?

236
00:19:06,799 --> 00:19:08,759
They say the man came from Ankara.

237
00:19:09,359 --> 00:19:11,960
Why did he come now,
after all these years?

238
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,720
Here comes your guy.

239
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:20,839
-He'll make you happy.
-Do you believe that?

240
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,319
No, even I don't.

241
00:19:27,599 --> 00:19:30,720
Teacher! How come the mighty Ankara
could only send one man?

242
00:19:31,759 --> 00:19:34,039
Were you expecting
an army with tanks and planes?

243
00:19:34,119 --> 00:19:36,720
No worries.
The important thing is that he is here.

244
00:19:38,039 --> 00:19:39,759
I've been to Ankara more than once.

245
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:46,759
Mr. Muzaffer will start talking when
the chief and Brother Cezmi stop talking.

246
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:49,119
-Teacher! It was Zulfikar's fault.
-What?

247
00:19:51,759 --> 00:19:53,400
Dear people of Elaldi Village,

248
00:19:55,119 --> 00:19:59,279
I'm going to talk to you about
the Ministry of Family's latest project.

