00:34:45,039 --> 00:34:46,760
You won't get anything, Ado.

498
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:49,360
For God's sake, Kibar.
What are you talking about?

499
00:34:50,079 --> 00:34:52,840
Are you listening to yourself, Kibar?

500
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:55,239
A woman has to give
everything she has to her husband.

501
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:59,159
Well, then the one you marry
should give you what she owns.

502
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:04,360
Because I swear to God, I won't!
You won't get anything from me.

503
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:05,880
I won't either.

504
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:07,840
Make a choice, Ado.

505
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:09,639
Her fields?

506
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:12,079
Or my fields?

507
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:20,320
ID

508
00:35:22,119 --> 00:35:25,440
What kind of fuckery is this?
These ID cards are not correct.

509
00:35:26,679 --> 00:35:28,599
It says I'm 18 years old and you are 72.

510
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:33,760
I've been using my dead aunt's ID.
What can I do?

511
00:35:35,199 --> 00:35:36,639
Just go to sleep.

512
00:35:48,039 --> 00:35:50,840
So they are going to marry
the ones on that list?

513
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,679
-Yes.
-Then what?

514
00:35:54,199 --> 00:35:57,039
-Then they will get the title deeds.
-And then?

515
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:00,199
They'll have the title deeds.

516
00:36:00,639 --> 00:36:02,639
What the…

517
00:36:03,039 --> 00:36:04,480
Fucking peasants.

518
00:36:06,320 --> 00:36:07,519
-Kismet.
-Yes?

519
00:36:07,599 --> 00:36:10,920
If that happens, they won't work
on our fields anymore.

520
00:36:11,039 --> 00:36:12,599
They won't work for us.

521
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,840
Do everything you can
and solve this problem.

522
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,119
How can I do that?

523
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:22,559
-Talk to the women.
-About what?

524
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:26,559
-Tell them not to get married.
-Sure. Anything else?

525
00:36:26,719 --> 00:36:29,880
Well, tell them marriage is a bad thing.

526
00:36:30,639 --> 00:36:31,960
Not for me.

527
00:36:32,280 --> 00:36:33,960
That's what you're going to tell them.

528
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:36,400
Kismet, please.

529
00:36:36,840 --> 00:36:39,920
Make it happen.
Persuade them not to get married.

530
00:36:40,199 --> 00:36:41,360
What if they reject it?

531
00:36:42,039 --> 00:36:47,320
You'll find a way.
You are the smartest woman of them all.

532
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:51,000
Well, everyone knows that.

533
00:36:51,719 --> 00:36:55,000
-Then go and see Kibar in the morning.
-No, I can't.

534
00:36:56,119 --> 00:36:58,039
-Why?
-Her house stinks.

535
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,599
-Good God!
-Yeah.

536
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,159
Kismet…

537
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:10,119
if you do this for me,
I'll buy you a golden bracelet.

538
00:37:11,679 --> 00:37:12,920
Not good enough.

539
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:17,480
-Two bracelets?
-Not enough.

540
00:37:19,079 --> 00:37:21,559
Fuck me, what else do you want,
you greedy woman?

541
00:37:22,960 --> 00:37:24,679
-I want a phone.
-What?

542
00:37:24,880 --> 00:37:26,079
Why would you want a phone?

543
00:37:26,159 --> 00:37:28,679
All of your relatives live nearby.
If you farted, they'd hear you.

544
00:37:29,159 --> 00:37:31,519
But I would be the only one with a phone.

545
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:35,800
Okay, fine.

546
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:37,800
I'll buy two phones for you.

547
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:40,880
You can hold the second one
next to your ass and talk to it.

548
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:49,519
In that case, I will destroy
all the potential marriages.

549
00:37:58,840 --> 00:38:01,079
What the hell? Azime is my match.

550
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,239
Dayibasi?

551
00:38:06,920 --> 00:38:09,559
-Speak of the devil and she shall appear.
-Huh?

552
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:12,800
What's up, Azime? What do you want?

553
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:15,480
My dad said I was your match.

554
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:18,519
-Yes. And?
-Huh?

555
00:38:20,079 --> 00:38:21,280
So?

556
00:38:21,679 --> 00:38:24,760
He said, "Don't bring that dog
into my home. Go to him and…"

557
00:38:29,760 --> 00:38:31,719
"And talk to him about marriage."

558
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:38,960
Azime, I don't want to get married.
I want to build a career for myself.

559
00:38:39,880 --> 00:38:40,880
Huh?

560
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:44,119
Azime, go back home. Go.

561
00:38:45,159 --> 00:38:46,480
Turn around!

562
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:49,679
Just keep walking in that direction. Go!

563
00:38:50,920 --> 00:38:51,960
Get out!

564
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:57,239
God damn it!
What kind of a project is this?

565
00:39:00,239 --> 00:39:02,400
I'm not used to sitting on the ground.

566
00:39:02,639 --> 00:39:04,239
My backside doesn't like it.

567
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:07,199
Did you wash your hands, Azime?

568
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:10,440
The dough seems clean.

569
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:14,760
Look, sipping tea,
but there's no side dishes.

570
00:39:15,039 --> 00:39:17,280
Can I get you some sugar candy?

571
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:20,039
-There is no candy.
-Yes, there's some in the kitchen.

572
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:22,599
That's for our guests.

573
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:24,360
Am I not a guest?

574
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:28,519
You rarely come here.
Why are you here now?

575
00:39:29,199 --> 00:39:32,239
I was just passing by with Cemile
and we decided to pay a visit. Right?

576
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:34,920
No. You came to me,
grabbed me and brought me here.

577
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:40,840
Dayibasi kind of rejected me.

578
00:39:42,239 --> 00:39:45,800
Don't worry. All these men are alike.
They are all evil.

579
00:39:46,119 --> 00:39:49,719
My husband, for example,
he forgets our wedding anniversary.

580
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:53,320
He forgets my birthday.
He doesn't care anymore.

581
00:39:53,679 --> 00:39:56,079
I have had enough!
I'm going to get a divorce.

582
00:39:56,239 --> 00:39:59,079
-Damn!
-Divorce? Has he got a second wife?

583
00:39:59,239 --> 00:40:01,840
-How can you say that, sister?
-Well, it is what it is.

584
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:04,079
Say "partner", it's more polite.

585
00:40:04,599 --> 00:40:08,639
No. He didn't get himself a second wife,
it's just that he isn't romantic.

586
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:11,239
-What?
-He isn't romantic.

587
00:40:12,599 --> 00:40:15,679
You know, I paid a visit
to my aunt in Ankara and--

588
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:16,840
They say that's a lie.

589
00:40:16,960 --> 00:40:20,159
That she was home with the curtains drawn,
pretending she had gone to Ankara.

590
00:40:30,559 --> 00:40:31,639
Who says that?

591
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:34,119
They are probably just haters
who are jealous of me.

592
00:40:36,039 --> 00:40:37,079
Anyway…

593
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:40,199
I went to Ankara.
Then I went to a movie theater.

594
00:40:40,719 --> 00:40:43,639
It was huge, just like my home.

595
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:46,199
A grand, flamboyant interior.

596
00:40:46,519 --> 00:40:49,000
In that movie, the man
asked the woman to marry him.

597
00:40:49,079 --> 00:40:50,719
But the way he asked…

598
00:40:51,159 --> 00:40:53,079
And Dayibasi called me "the devil".

599
00:40:53,719 --> 00:40:55,679
The man was lying on the floor.

600
00:40:56,119 --> 00:40:57,760
Ado was also lying on the floor yesterday.

601
00:40:58,440 --> 00:41:00,519
No, not like that.

602
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:05,360
The man was on his knee,
his other knee was facing forward,

603
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:07,199
and he bowed before the woman.

604
00:41:07,599 --> 00:41:09,760
-Like this.
-In that position?

605
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:12,159
Not really.

606
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:16,599
But he bought a fancy ring for the woman,
with a huge diamond on it.

607
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:19,960
-Damn…
-And he says, "Will you marry me?"

608
00:41:20,119 --> 00:41:21,599
Asking her a question.

609
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,119
-Asking who?
-The woman.

610
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:29,320
Why? He should be asking
the woman's father.

611
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,800
Movies are so fake.

612
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:35,239
Not really. That is what
the men in Ankara are really like.

613
00:41:35,639 --> 00:41:38,599
They say "dear", "baby",
"honey" to the women there.

614
00:41:38,760 --> 00:41:40,760
They say, "I love you."

615
00:41:41,159 --> 00:41:42,559
It's so different there.

616
00:41:44,480 --> 00:41:45,559
Right…

617
00:42:01,079 --> 00:42:02,760
-Sister.
-What's up?

618
00:42:03,159 --> 00:42:04,480
-Tell you what.
-What?

619
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:08,079
I don't want to marry Israfil.

620
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:10,880
-What is wrong with Israfil?
-I love Mahmut.

621
00:42:11,239 --> 00:42:12,960
-That can't happen.
-Why not?

622
00:42:13,599 --> 00:42:16,519
-He's not on the list.
-So the list gets to decide, not me?

623
00:42:17,079 --> 00:42:19,320
That's the will of Ankara.
We can't object to it.

624
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:22,800
I don't want him. I don't love him.
Why can't you understand?

625
00:42:23,199 --> 00:42:25,440
You don't have to love him.
You'll get used to him.

626
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:29,719
You'll be his partner. You'll collaborate,
but you will get used to him.

627
00:42:30,079 --> 00:42:33,760
At some point you might even
want to see him dead.

628
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:37,199
Sometimes you will hate him,
but you will get used to him anyway.

629
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:40,599
It doesn't matter if you love him or not.
Marriage is like shopping.

630
00:42:40,800 --> 00:42:43,000
Give and take. Give and take.

631
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:46,199
Take more, give less. You see?

632
00:42:47,239 --> 00:42:48,800
Now, get up. It's time to cook.

633
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:50,880
We'll go to Cemile's house
to prepare the food.

634
00:42:52,199 --> 00:42:54,679
-Mom, I'm hungry.
-You little brat, just move.

635
00:42:56,920 --> 00:43:00,039
-Hi, guys.
-Hi.

636
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:12,880
Brother Suleyman,
I could use some cold water here.

637
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,159
Go and get it yourself.

638
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:15,599
I'm in a tough spot.

639
00:43:17,840 --> 00:43:18,880
Who isn't?

640
00:43:19,599 --> 00:43:20,960
No, I don't get it.

641
00:43:21,239 --> 00:43:23,840
Seyhan's grandmother and my aunt
are somehow related.

642
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:26,400
But that doesn't make us relatives.

643
00:43:26,880 --> 00:43:30,000
Cousins, nieces, those are relatives.

644
00:43:30,079 --> 00:43:31,599
-You know?
-Well said.

645
00:43:31,719 --> 00:43:35,440
It's a distant relation.
I don't understand how we are related.

646
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:38,119
We are not relatives, just acquaintances.

647
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:40,320
Well, at least you have a match.

648
00:43:42,039 --> 00:43:44,800
Damn you, Dad.
Why did you marry one of our relatives?

649
00:43:45,599 --> 00:43:47,800
I wonder if we can officially reject
my mom as a relative.

650
00:43:47,880 --> 00:43:49,199
She's a pain in the ass anyway.

651
00:43:49,679 --> 00:43:52,719
-Is that possible?
-I don't know.

652
00:43:54,719 --> 00:43:55,960
Right.

653
00:44:00,440 --> 00:44:03,400
What are you looking at, bro?
It's not like I burnt your field down.

654
00:44:03,559 --> 00:44:05,079
You burnt my heart down with your match.

655
00:44:05,440 --> 00:44:07,840
Well, people get what they deserve, huh?

656
00:44:08,079 --> 00:44:09,440
What the fuck is that?

657
00:44:09,719 --> 00:44:12,280
You didn't say anything
when you were matched with Melike.

658
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:15,280
-Were you interested in her?
-You have a point.

659
00:44:15,559 --> 00:44:18,559
-Shut up, Israfil.
-Why?

660
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:22,320
-What happens if I don't?
-Let the real men speak.

661
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:24,559
People who don't respect
other's lovers aren't real men.

662
00:44:25,239 --> 00:44:27,199
And you're a real man? Is that it?

663
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:28,880
That's right.

664
00:44:29,119 --> 00:44:31,400
-Watch your mouth.
-Put that hand down.

665
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:41,920
I hope one of them gets killed,
so that I can have one of the girls.

666
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:47,800
What are you doing, Seyhan?
The dough is gone.

667
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:50,599
Always blaming others, right?
What about you?

668
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:52,719
-Seyhan, look here.
-So what?

669
00:44:52,920 --> 00:44:55,320
-Just leave it.
-My hand!

670
00:44:56,079 --> 00:44:57,800
People get what they deserve, eventually.

671
00:44:58,199 --> 00:45:00,119
Oh, do you like to see me suffer?

672
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,320
-Yeah, I love it.
-Is that right?

673
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:03,960
That's right.

674
00:45:04,519 --> 00:45:06,440
Come on. Taste my pain then.

675
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,639
-Leave it!
-You…

676
00:45:08,760 --> 00:45:09,880
-Stop it!
-Don't!

677
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:11,000
What the hell?

678
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:12,480
Let her go!

679
00:45:13,960 --> 00:45:17,480
Guys! What the hell are you doing?

680
00:45:17,920 --> 00:45:19,239
Guys!

681
00:45:19,760 --> 00:45:21,840
What is going on here? Stop it!

682
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:25,320
Fuck it, Teacher.
Let me smash his face in.

683
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:27,440
I'll make him pay
for taking an interest in my lover.

684
00:45:27,559 --> 00:45:30,519
-Calm down.
-I didn't do that!

685
00:45:30,639 --> 00:45:33,360
I've loved Bedevi since childhood.
I want her.

686
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:37,480
To hell with those title deeds
and weddings!

687
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:54,679
Brother Orhan, you're the oldest one here.
Why didn't you do something?

688
00:45:55,440 --> 00:45:56,880
I'm not in the mood.

689
00:46:00,360 --> 00:46:01,599
What's their problem anyway?

690
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:03,599
It's about the weddings.

691
00:46:04,119 --> 00:46:06,440
Uncle Orhan, do you have
a problem with your hearing?

692
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:09,760
And he smiles.

693
00:46:11,079 --> 00:46:12,079
This guy…

694
00:46:12,159 --> 00:46:13,800
-Stop it!
-Let her go!

695
00:46:13,960 --> 00:46:16,519
Leave her be! Stop it!

696
00:46:16,719 --> 00:46:18,519
What's your problem? What the hell?

697
00:46:19,239 --> 00:46:21,480
-What is going on?
-Mom!

698
00:46:21,679 --> 00:46:22,920
Let that slut explain it!

699
00:46:23,079 --> 00:46:25,400
Watch your mouth, Melike!

700
00:46:25,719 --> 00:46:27,079
Come to your senses!

701
00:46:27,599 --> 00:46:30,639
-Don't take an interest in others' lovers!
-I don't!

702
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:34,039
I wasn't matched with my lover either!
Let go! Back off!

703
00:46:34,280 --> 00:46:36,440
To hell with title deeds and weddings!
Let go of me!

704
00:46:36,559 --> 00:46:39,800
Damn you all! I'll end up killing myself!

705
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:46,119
Nobody wants this,
so stop upsetting each other.

706
00:46:46,320 --> 00:46:48,480
Upset? What do you mean, Zeynep?

707
00:46:48,559 --> 00:46:51,039
-We're all crying rivers here.
-Just shut up.

708
00:46:51,639 --> 00:46:53,280
My mom wants to see you.

709
00:47:00,920 --> 00:47:02,039
Mr. Muzaffer!

710
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:05,039
What are you doing here?

711
00:47:05,639 --> 00:47:07,079
Come here, Teacher Salih.

712
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:10,679
I wanted to look around,
but there is not much to see.

713
00:47:11,039 --> 00:47:12,679
Yeah, it's a small place.

714
00:47:13,400 --> 00:47:14,960
"Yeah"? Your language is deteriorating.

715
00:47:16,360 --> 00:47:19,079
It doesn't deteriorate,
Mr. Muzaffer, it just changes.

716
00:47:19,440 --> 00:47:21,119
The key thing is to understand each other.

717
00:47:21,440 --> 00:47:24,360
-If it wasn't, what would a mute do?
-You are right.

718
00:47:26,880 --> 00:47:30,000
-The bridge is gone.
-Yes.

719
00:47:31,599 --> 00:47:35,280
It was not safe,
so the state had to demolish it.

720
00:47:35,440 --> 00:47:36,719
But they didn't build a new one.

721
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:39,760
Teacher! Teacher Salih!

722
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:41,599
Boys, what is it?

723
00:47:41,880 --> 00:47:44,360
I told you not to come up here again.

724
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:47,639
-What's going on?
-My dad wants to see you tomorrow.

725
00:47:48,239 --> 00:47:49,239
Yes, I know.

726
00:47:49,599 --> 00:47:51,400
He said, "That asshole
had better remember."

727
00:47:52,280 --> 00:47:54,519
-Asshole?
-That's what he said.

728
00:47:59,599 --> 00:48:01,119
All right, okay.

729
00:48:02,159 --> 00:48:03,920
Let's go, Mr. Muzaffer.

730
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:05,519
Go back home.

731
00:48:09,519 --> 00:48:12,000
-Dad didn't say "asshole".
-No, that was me.

732
00:48:22,360 --> 00:48:23,440
Zeynep?

733
00:48:33,760 --> 00:48:35,440
I'll wait for you over there, Salih.

734
00:48:39,119 --> 00:48:41,719
Look at him. That evil bastard.

735
00:48:43,679 --> 00:48:46,199
-Why would you say that?
-This is all because of him.

736
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:49,239
Everyone is upset.
Nobody is with the one they love.

737
00:48:49,920 --> 00:48:52,599
What about you? Are you upset?

738
00:48:53,920 --> 00:48:56,519
I feel sad for my sister and friends.

739
00:48:57,920 --> 00:48:59,320
Aren't you?

740
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:06,960
Anyway, I'll go get the kids.

741
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:14,599
Hey! I told you not to come here.

742
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:16,920
What the hell are you doing here again?

743
