01:08:51,119 --> 01:08:54,119
So everything else is right, it's just
this situation that's wrong. Is that it?

991
01:08:54,680 --> 01:08:56,399
Nobody is happy.

992
01:09:09,000 --> 01:09:11,359
They'll get used to it, Salih.
Change is hard.

993
01:09:13,039 --> 01:09:14,159
It's tough.

994
01:09:14,960 --> 01:09:15,960
It's tough.

995
01:09:17,399 --> 01:09:18,800
-Cevo.
-Yeah?

996
01:09:20,479 --> 01:09:23,720
-You won't touch Bedevi, right?
-Good God.

997
01:09:24,880 --> 01:09:28,840
-Your beloved is like a sister to me.
-You are right.

998
01:09:29,199 --> 01:09:31,560
-I have an idea.
-What is it, Mahmut?

999
01:09:31,760 --> 01:09:34,359
Call the girls here.
I'll explain it to everyone.

1000
01:09:34,640 --> 01:09:35,680
Go on.

1001
01:09:48,359 --> 01:09:49,800
Ask Kevser for my hand in marriage.

1002
01:09:53,760 --> 01:09:55,000
Ask Kevser?

1003
01:09:57,520 --> 01:09:59,399
I won't fucking marry you. I won't.

1004
01:09:59,920 --> 01:10:01,239
I'll just marry someone else.

1005
01:10:07,720 --> 01:10:09,880
In Ankara, women request dates,
as far as I've heard.

1006
01:10:09,960 --> 01:10:11,800
-What?
-In Ankara, women--

1007
01:10:11,880 --> 01:10:13,000
You already told me that.

1008
01:10:13,560 --> 01:10:15,039
Let's go, Mr. Muzaffer.

1009
01:10:15,279 --> 01:10:17,920
No, I want to listen to him. Tell me.

1010
01:10:18,600 --> 01:10:20,840
I'm curious. How many girls
have asked you out in Ankara?

1011
01:10:20,960 --> 01:10:22,119
None.

1012
01:10:23,039 --> 01:10:26,199
Well, judging from your looks,
I guess that's normal.

1013
01:10:26,399 --> 01:10:28,840
-Sorry?
-I mean, that's normal.

1014
01:10:29,239 --> 01:10:32,479
-If you don't have any other--
-I do, Teacher.

1015
01:10:32,800 --> 01:10:35,039
I have a problem.
Mr. Minister, please come closer.

1016
01:10:36,800 --> 01:10:38,279
Come and look me in the eyes.

1017
01:10:38,920 --> 01:10:40,680
One of my eyes was green.

1018
01:10:41,399 --> 01:10:42,600
I lost so much weight.

1019
01:10:43,479 --> 01:10:46,039
-The other lost its color.
-What are you talking about?

1020
01:10:46,840 --> 01:10:51,359
Do you know anyone in Ankara
who might want to marry me?

1021
01:10:52,800 --> 01:10:54,039
-No.
-Huseyin.

1022
01:10:54,840 --> 01:10:55,880
Please, get up.

1023
01:10:57,920 --> 01:10:59,479
I'd better go now.

1024
01:11:05,199 --> 01:11:07,359
There are a lot of crazy people
in this village.

1025
01:11:08,159 --> 01:11:10,680
There are, unfortunately.

1026
01:11:15,000 --> 01:11:16,640
Why is this happening, Grandmother?

1027
01:11:19,199 --> 01:11:23,279
Love is lived a little differently here,
my lovely girl.

1028
01:11:23,800 --> 01:11:26,199
But I can't live without my beloved.

1029
01:11:27,600 --> 01:11:29,880
Of course you can.

1030
01:11:31,640 --> 01:11:34,479
How would you know what it means
to be without your beloved?

1031
01:11:37,439 --> 01:11:38,520
I do know.

1032
01:11:40,560 --> 01:11:44,119
When a girl gets in bed
with someone she doesn't love…

1033
01:11:45,680 --> 01:11:47,359
even the man's mustache bothers the girl.

1034
01:11:48,800 --> 01:11:50,199
Everything bothers her.

1035
01:11:52,840 --> 01:11:55,399
Around here, we don't really get
to marry the ones we love.

1036
01:11:57,800 --> 01:12:00,000
Your mom didn't want
to marry your dad either.

1037
01:12:01,840 --> 01:12:03,439
"I'll kill myself," she said.

1038
01:12:04,640 --> 01:12:06,439
But she didn't.

1039
01:12:11,319 --> 01:12:15,560
Your grandfather approved the marriage
and we couldn't say anything.

1040
01:12:17,840 --> 01:12:21,880
Your mom cried rivers,
but she married him.

1041
01:12:23,800 --> 01:12:26,119
And then you girls came into the world.

1042
01:12:55,800 --> 01:12:56,880
Cevat?

1043
01:12:58,800 --> 01:12:59,920
Cevat!

1044
01:13:01,399 --> 01:13:03,239
-What's wrong?
-Huh?

1045
01:13:03,720 --> 01:13:05,800
-What's going on?
-What?

1046
01:13:07,479 --> 01:13:08,960
Wait. We'll be right there.

1047
01:13:20,439 --> 01:13:21,479
Seyhan.

1048
01:13:22,159 --> 01:13:24,920
I need to get food from the store,
but I'm scared. Come with me.

1049
01:13:25,159 --> 01:13:27,560
Just leave me be, Zeynep.
Can't you see I'm in pain?

1050
01:13:27,880 --> 01:13:30,159
I'm telling you, I'm scared. Come with me!

1051
01:13:30,239 --> 01:13:32,680
-Just take someone else with you.
-Get up, Seyhan!

1052
01:13:35,680 --> 01:13:38,439
Go on, Seyhan. Get up.

1053
01:13:41,560 --> 01:13:43,319
Stop it. Come on.

1054
01:13:43,920 --> 01:13:45,199
Cevat is waiting.

1055
01:13:45,680 --> 01:13:46,800
-Where?
-Move it.

1056
01:13:58,119 --> 01:13:59,279
Zeynep.

1057
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:03,640
Evening.

1058
01:14:04,119 --> 01:14:05,319
Evening.

1059
01:14:08,159 --> 01:14:09,279
Look at me.

1060
01:14:09,520 --> 01:14:11,920
If you're planning
to take the girls away--

1061
01:14:12,000 --> 01:14:13,279
Take them away? No.

1062
01:14:13,920 --> 01:14:16,479
Where would we take them to?
How could we take them away?

1063
01:14:17,359 --> 01:14:18,920
Okay, that's fine.

1064
01:14:19,560 --> 01:14:22,119
Tell me then. Why are you here?

1065
01:14:27,600 --> 01:14:29,720
Fine, okay. I get it.

1066
01:14:30,079 --> 01:14:33,720
I'll be waiting right there.
But make it quick, okay?

1067
01:14:33,920 --> 01:14:35,199
-Okay.
-Yeah.

1068
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:44,920
So, guys, if they want to separate us
just to collect some title deeds

1069
01:14:45,000 --> 01:14:46,439
then we need a plan.

1070
01:14:46,680 --> 01:14:48,119
-Right.
-Of course.

1071
01:14:48,560 --> 01:14:51,399
I don't get it.
Seyhan and I can't be relatives.

1072
01:14:51,520 --> 01:14:54,000
Her grandmother and my auntie--

1073
01:14:54,079 --> 01:14:56,359
-Shut up for God's sake, Cevat.
-God.

1074
01:14:56,520 --> 01:14:59,279
We'll stay married until we get the deeds.
Then we'll get a divorce.

1075
01:14:59,359 --> 01:15:01,399
Who keeps the title deeds
when we get divorced?

1076
01:15:01,479 --> 01:15:02,760
The man or the woman?

1077
01:15:03,079 --> 01:15:04,760
Divorces aren't common here, Bedevi.

1078
01:15:04,880 --> 01:15:06,119
-True.
-It doesn't matter.

1079
01:15:06,359 --> 01:15:08,119
From now on, it'll be common.

1080
01:15:08,279 --> 01:15:10,880
How does one get a divorce anyway?

1081
01:15:10,960 --> 01:15:12,399
Well, you go…

1082
01:15:12,840 --> 01:15:14,920
I mean, I don't really know.

1083
01:15:15,399 --> 01:15:18,720
We'll be reunited with our lovers.
The rest is Ankara's problem.

1084
01:15:18,920 --> 01:15:21,039
Murat is the only one for me.

1085
01:15:21,319 --> 01:15:23,680
Don't get ahead of yourself.
What if there are kids?

1086
01:15:32,479 --> 01:15:33,720
I don't really know.

1087
01:15:34,520 --> 01:15:36,800
Anyway, Israfil?

1088
01:15:37,319 --> 01:15:42,359
We'll get married, but you'll still
treat me like a sister, right?

1089
01:15:42,720 --> 01:15:45,079
Yes, I swear. You're like a sister to me.

1090
01:15:45,720 --> 01:15:48,279
Besides, I'm in love with someone else.

1091
01:15:52,920 --> 01:15:54,840
-Whatever.
-Let's go.

1092
01:15:55,159 --> 01:15:56,479
-Take it easy.
-See you later.

1093
01:15:56,560 --> 01:15:57,800
Have a good night.

1094
01:16:00,079 --> 01:16:01,920
Go on!

1095
01:16:19,479 --> 01:16:25,319
I just comb my hair, mind my own business

1096
01:16:25,479 --> 01:16:31,119
I just want my lover
I'm in flames, day and night

1097
01:16:31,520 --> 01:16:37,119
What do I have to be ashamed of?

1098
01:16:37,479 --> 01:16:43,159
To hell with Ankara's project
I already have a lover

1099
01:16:54,600 --> 01:16:58,840
Ado will find another woman
and marry her because of you.

1100
01:16:58,920 --> 01:17:01,159
It's because of you. You're younger.

1101
01:17:01,279 --> 01:17:03,439
The older one gets to get married.
I'm the older one here.

1102
01:17:03,560 --> 01:17:06,800
I deserve to be married to him.
I always carry Ado's burden.

1103
01:17:08,439 --> 01:17:12,359
Mom, run! Deva fell in the oven.

1104
01:17:12,600 --> 01:17:14,600
-The oven was on!
-What?

1105
01:17:14,920 --> 01:17:16,079
Deva!

1106
01:17:16,359 --> 01:17:17,520
Deva!

1107
01:17:17,840 --> 01:17:20,199
Deva!

1108
01:17:20,399 --> 01:17:21,720
Don't worry! I'm here, my girl!

1109
01:17:22,319 --> 01:17:24,079
-Deva!
-Deva!

1110
01:17:25,680 --> 01:17:26,840
She is not here.

1111
01:17:26,960 --> 01:17:29,920
Deva!

1112
01:17:31,039 --> 01:17:33,079
-She is fine.
-Where have you been, baby?

1113
01:17:33,479 --> 01:17:34,920
You're fine, dear.

1114
01:17:35,199 --> 01:17:38,760
She's perfectly fine.
There's nothing wrong with her.

1115
01:17:40,000 --> 01:17:42,000
You fucking brat! Did you lie?

1116
01:17:42,199 --> 01:17:43,960
-Son of a bastard!
-Bastard!

1117
01:17:44,159 --> 01:17:45,359
Shameless brat.

1118
01:17:46,279 --> 01:17:47,359
Come here, baby.

1119
01:17:48,600 --> 01:17:50,880
Thank God, she is fine.

1120
01:17:52,880 --> 01:17:55,119
-Put the cream on.
-Stay still, I'm putting it on.

1121
01:17:59,199 --> 01:18:00,439
Good God!

1122
01:18:01,079 --> 01:18:04,199
Have you lost your mind?
Why would you put your hand in the oven?

1123
01:18:04,479 --> 01:18:06,119
Even this kid is smarter than you.

1124
01:18:06,600 --> 01:18:08,640
See, she didn't touch the oven.

1125
01:18:09,039 --> 01:18:12,239
What could I do? I was worried about her.

1126
01:18:12,720 --> 01:18:15,520
Sister, are you in pain?

1127
01:18:16,399 --> 01:18:18,439
No, of course not. I love fire.

1128
01:18:19,760 --> 01:18:22,199
Send me to Hell when I die
so I can burn in peace.

1129
01:18:22,520 --> 01:18:24,760
Fire is good, right? Blow on it.

1130
01:18:26,039 --> 01:18:27,199
God.

1131
01:18:28,399 --> 01:18:29,800
-Sister.
-What?

1132
01:18:30,720 --> 01:18:32,319
You can marry Ado.

1133
01:18:34,359 --> 01:18:35,479
Why?

1134
01:18:35,720 --> 01:18:39,920
Sister, your home is my home.
Your fields are my fields.

1135
01:18:40,159 --> 01:18:43,479
Your kids are my kids too, dear sister.
We're a family, right?

1136
01:18:52,640 --> 01:18:53,600
Huh?

1137
01:18:55,319 --> 01:18:56,479
What now?

1138
01:19:11,680 --> 01:19:13,560
Have you all got it?

1139
01:19:13,760 --> 01:19:14,840
Teacher.

1140
01:19:16,319 --> 01:19:19,079
-I'm working here, Chief.
-That's okay.

1141
01:19:19,199 --> 01:19:20,680
Kids don't bother me.

1142
01:19:20,880 --> 01:19:23,640
They are kids, they're fine.
Now, look at me.

1143
01:19:23,760 --> 01:19:26,600
How is the process going?
How did they respond?

1144
01:19:27,159 --> 01:19:29,560
Everything is fine. I have their IDs.

1145
01:19:30,760 --> 01:19:31,880
Why?

1146
01:19:32,199 --> 01:19:33,960
Why are you even here?

1147
01:19:34,880 --> 01:19:35,920
Oh, right.

1148
01:19:36,800 --> 01:19:39,560
This is the letter you wanted
to send to Ankara.

1149
01:19:39,800 --> 01:19:43,680
I thought Mr. Muzaffer can take it
to Ankara, if he's still here.

1150
01:19:43,840 --> 01:19:45,880
-Has he gone?
-That won't be necessary.

1151
01:19:47,199 --> 01:19:49,159
Sorry for interrupting the lesson,
but it's urgent.

1152
01:19:49,640 --> 01:19:51,920
That's fine.
I already interrupted the lesson.

1153
01:19:53,079 --> 01:19:54,760
I'm here to collect the IDs.

1154
01:19:55,520 --> 01:19:58,760
I have some of them here,
but the rest are at my house.

1155
01:20:00,520 --> 01:20:03,119
-Okay, bring them here.
-Sure. Let me take the kids home.

1156
01:20:03,199 --> 01:20:08,199
No way. That won't be nice for them.
The kids should stay on course here.

1157
01:20:08,319 --> 01:20:11,239
I can teach them a few lessons.
I love children.

1158
01:20:12,560 --> 01:20:13,760
Come on, Salih.

1159
01:20:16,039 --> 01:20:17,000
All right, okay.

1160
01:20:28,159 --> 01:20:30,079
You there! Come here at once.

1161
01:20:30,560 --> 01:20:32,119
Take these papers.

1162
01:20:32,600 --> 01:20:34,039
Give some of them to your friends.

1163
01:20:34,439 --> 01:20:37,399
So the first lesson
is about folding paper.

1164
01:20:37,640 --> 01:20:40,119
Now, fold that paper like a cup,

1165
01:20:40,199 --> 01:20:43,119
so I can put cookies in them
and sell them.

1166
01:20:43,199 --> 01:20:44,680
Got it? Then let's begin.

1167
01:20:44,800 --> 01:20:47,560
Get to work. You too.
Give the others some paper.

1168
01:20:47,640 --> 01:20:50,000
Come on! Hurry up, lads.

1169
01:20:53,159 --> 01:20:56,199
Damn! Ido, Come here.

1170
01:20:56,840 --> 01:20:58,880
Take this letter to the teacher. Hurry!

1171
01:21:03,920 --> 01:21:05,920
Take this ID and give it to the teacher.

1172
01:21:06,680 --> 01:21:08,279
But this is Kehribar's ID.

1173
01:21:08,680 --> 01:21:10,039
Yes, it is.

1174
01:21:11,159 --> 01:21:12,720
She deserves to marry you.

1175
01:21:12,800 --> 01:21:15,199
Poor thing, she's young
and has a lot on her shoulders.

1176
01:21:21,000 --> 01:21:23,720
Your mustache bothers me, but not her.

1177
01:21:31,800 --> 01:21:33,960
Where are you going, Ido?

1178
01:21:34,760 --> 01:21:35,800
To find the teacher.

1179
01:21:37,159 --> 01:21:39,680
-Okay. What is that?
-Teacher's letter.

1180
01:21:40,600 --> 01:21:42,520
-Where is he?
-He went home.

1181
01:21:42,840 --> 01:21:46,319
Okay, give it to me.
I'll take it to him. You go back to class.

1182
01:21:46,439 --> 01:21:49,439
-But don't read it.
-That'd be shameful. Go ahead.

1183
01:21:55,119 --> 01:21:56,520
FROM SALIH OZTURK
TO THE MINISTRY OF FAMILY

1184
01:22:02,760 --> 01:22:05,319
"To the Republic of Turkey's
Ministry of Family,

1185
01:22:05,720 --> 01:22:08,720
I've been working as a teacher
in the village of Elaldi for three years."

1186
01:22:09,119 --> 01:22:11,680
"This is the 38th letter
I have sent to the Ministry."

1187
01:22:12,359 --> 01:22:15,399
"I reported what happened in the village
after the collapse

1188
01:22:15,479 --> 01:22:19,359
of the Freedom and Equality Bridge."

1189
01:22:19,920 --> 01:22:25,119
"The people here are so cut off
from the outside world."

1190
01:22:25,800 --> 01:22:27,479
"Since the bridge's collapse,

1191
01:22:27,600 --> 01:22:31,279
the villagers have resorted to
marrying their cousins."

1192
01:22:31,399 --> 01:22:33,239
"And these types of marriages
cause problems,

1193
01:22:33,319 --> 01:22:36,079
not just for the families,
but also for the kids."

1194
01:22:36,720 --> 01:22:40,319
"I would like the Ministry
to do something about this."

1195
01:22:41,520 --> 01:22:43,720
"I kindly request
that you take the necessary action."

1196
01:22:44,680 --> 01:22:47,960
"Teacher Salih Ozturk."

1197
01:22:54,319 --> 01:22:55,600
Teacher Salih!

1198
01:23:01,239 --> 01:23:02,399
You did this.

1199
01:23:08,560 --> 01:23:11,680
I did it for you.
I did it so we could be together.

1200
01:23:12,319 --> 01:23:13,840
But everybody else is sad.

1201
01:23:16,079 --> 01:23:17,479
I didn't know that would happen.

1202
01:23:18,000 --> 01:23:21,359
How can I be happy with you
while there is so much sadness around?

1203
01:23:21,680 --> 01:23:23,359
I can't. We can't be happy.

1204
01:23:24,119 --> 01:23:25,279
Not anymore.

1205
01:23:33,079 --> 01:23:34,520
What is it, Teacher Salih?

1206
01:23:36,239 --> 01:23:39,520
I caused this mess, Mr. Muzaffer.

1207
01:23:39,960 --> 01:23:43,560
We can talk about that later.
We need to get the IDs there at once.

1208
01:23:43,640 --> 01:23:45,239
-Let's go.
-You go ahead.

1209
01:23:46,399 --> 01:23:48,439
I don't want to be
part of this mess anymore.

1210
01:23:50,880 --> 01:23:54,600
I don't want to influence
others' lives to get what I want.

1211
01:23:54,880 --> 01:23:55,880
What do you mean?

1212
01:23:59,159 --> 01:24:01,640
I didn't understand them,
yet I wanted them to understand me.

1213
01:24:04,319 --> 01:24:08,520
How can someone understand you
when you don't understand them?

1214
01:24:10,680 --> 01:24:11,880
They can't.

1215
01:24:14,000 --> 01:24:15,399
Ankara!

1216
01:24:17,600 --> 01:24:19,840
Mr. Minister!

1217
01:24:20,399 --> 01:24:21,479
Mr. Minister.

1218
01:24:23,399 --> 01:24:25,840
Minister? I'm just a civil servant.

1219
01:24:27,319 --> 01:24:29,279
Mr. Civil Servant, please.

1220
01:24:29,560 --> 01:24:31,800
Let's go to Ankara
to find me a suitable wife.

1221
01:24:31,880 --> 01:24:33,199
You must know suitable candidates.

1222
01:24:34,000 --> 01:24:35,880
I'll pay for the bride, if necessary.

1223
01:24:37,479 --> 01:24:40,399
I can also give away three of my sheep.

1224
01:24:49,479 --> 01:24:53,039
But the girl doesn't want him.
She says she'll kill herself if needs be.

1225
01:24:53,920 --> 01:24:57,239
You have to do whatever I say.
Girls can't choose their husbands!

1226
01:24:57,920 --> 01:25:01,279
The teacher and that Muzaffer guy
can both go to Hell.

1227
01:25:41,720 --> 01:25:42,720
OATH OF LOVE

1228
01:26:42,359 --> 01:26:44,640
Zeynep. Come and take care of me.

1229
01:26:45,399 --> 01:26:46,840
Look, I look wonderful.

1230
01:26:49,000 --> 01:26:50,359
You're so beautiful.

1231
01:26:50,840 --> 01:26:53,000
What about me, Zeynep?

1232
01:26:54,920 --> 01:26:56,520
You look so beautiful too.

1233
01:27:00,119 --> 01:27:01,600
You're all so beautiful.

1234
01:27:06,359 --> 01:27:07,640
I wish things were different.

1235
01:27:08,800 --> 01:27:09,920
But here we are.

1236
01:27:10,520 --> 01:27:13,399
Whatever. Don't fret, Zeynep. It's fate.

1237
01:27:17,359 --> 01:27:19,880
Don't worry about us, Zeynep.

1238
01:27:20,000 --> 01:27:23,520
We've already found a solution.
The men promised they won't touch us.

1239
01:27:23,840 --> 01:27:28,119
We will reunite with our lovers
once we get the title deeds and lands.

1240
01:27:29,000 --> 01:27:30,000
Hopefully.

1241
01:27:31,720 --> 01:27:32,960
Hopefully.

1242
01:27:43,239 --> 01:27:45,239
It's all because of me.

1243
01:27:47,199 --> 01:27:49,840
-What is wrong with Zeynep?
-She's probably worried about us.

1244
01:27:50,159 --> 01:27:52,960
And she is next in line to get married.
Maybe she's afraid.

1245
01:27:57,840 --> 01:27:59,159
Ladies.

1246
01:27:59,319 --> 01:28:01,880
Oh, my beautiful girls.

1247
01:28:02,079 --> 01:28:03,680
Praise be!

1248
01:28:03,920 --> 01:28:06,039
You look fantastic.

1249
01:28:06,840 --> 01:28:08,640
But the men have tricked you.

1250
01:28:09,920 --> 01:28:13,199
-They wouldn't trick us.
-Shut up. What do you know?

1251
01:28:17,520 --> 01:28:19,920
It's impossible
to marry the ones you love.

1252
01:28:20,880 --> 01:28:23,399
None of your mothers
loved none of your fathers.

1253
01:28:23,720 --> 01:28:27,039
But all of your fathers had their way
with your mothers, obviously.

1254
01:28:27,319 --> 01:28:30,239
I also had to let my lover
be with someone else.

1255
01:28:31,039 --> 01:28:34,319
And I had to let someone else's lover
have his way with me.

1256
01:28:35,840 --> 01:28:37,399
All men are the same.

1257
01:28:38,399 --> 01:28:41,159
Of course they will touch you
and have their way with you.

1258
01:28:42,680 --> 01:28:45,359
You will be wasted tonight.

1259
01:29:12,600 --> 01:29:14,840
Have you seen the looks on their faces?
Hello there.

1260
01:29:16,520 --> 01:29:19,880
Look! Look at those brave young men!

1261
01:29:21,560 --> 01:29:24,680
I brought you some liquor, guys.

1262
01:29:24,880 --> 01:29:27,359
I don't know,
maybe it will give you some courage.

1263
01:29:29,640 --> 01:29:31,079
Listen to me.

1264
01:29:31,159 --> 01:29:33,640
If you have any questions
about anything, just ask me.

1265
01:29:33,720 --> 01:29:35,199
I'll teach you how to seal the deal.

1266
01:29:35,319 --> 01:29:37,880
-I'm about to smash your face in.
-Whoa! Look, fat boy.

1267
01:29:38,039 --> 01:29:40,600
You are all grown up.

1268
01:29:40,680 --> 01:29:43,880
You're about to get married
and you'll have kids soon.

1269
01:29:44,319 --> 01:29:45,800
But you still don't have manners.

1270
01:29:46,039 --> 01:29:48,119
Stop fucking with the boys, Cezmi.

1271
01:29:48,279 --> 01:29:51,399
In the end, they are marrying
each other's girlfriends.

1272
01:29:52,920 --> 01:29:55,840
You are right. Poor boys. Hey! Good God!

1273
01:29:55,960 --> 01:29:58,760
-Go away before I crack your skull open.
-Come here.

1274
01:29:59,199 --> 01:30:00,199
Oh, the mighty fatty!

1275
01:30:04,399 --> 01:30:06,680
-Hit it!
-Come here.

1276
01:30:07,119 --> 01:30:09,600
Come here, you dumb-ass!

1277
01:30:10,800 --> 01:30:12,920
Come here. Start dancing with us.

1278
01:31:48,600 --> 01:31:49,640
Salih!

1279
01:31:51,960 --> 01:31:53,279
Where are you going?

1280
01:31:55,319 --> 01:31:58,359
-Back where I came from.
-So you're running away, huh?

1281
01:31:59,520 --> 01:32:02,720
Leaving the village and the kids behind
and running away?

1282
01:32:04,800 --> 01:32:07,439
-I screwed everything up.
-Yes, you did.

1283
01:32:10,359 --> 01:32:11,640
You're a coward.

1284
01:32:17,720 --> 01:32:19,079
That's why I'm leaving.

1285
01:32:21,720 --> 01:32:22,720
Go!

1286
01:32:23,920 --> 01:32:25,840
Go away, Teacher Salih! Go!

1287
01:33:10,079 --> 01:33:11,520
What are you doing, Salih?

1288
01:33:12,560 --> 01:33:14,000
Wait a second!

1289
01:33:19,560 --> 01:33:20,640
Stop!

1290
01:33:21,159 --> 01:33:22,239
What the fuck's going on?

1291
01:33:28,800 --> 01:33:30,640
I'm in love with Zeynep.

1292
01:33:37,760 --> 01:33:42,600
I am asking you to give me
her hand in marriage.

1293
01:33:46,479 --> 01:33:47,760
-Uncle Ado!
-What?

1294
01:33:48,119 --> 01:33:49,520
Come quickly!

1295
01:33:49,640 --> 01:33:51,479
-The girls are going to kill themselves!
-What?

1296
01:33:51,560 --> 01:33:53,000
-Where are they?
-The girls?

1297
01:33:53,119 --> 01:33:54,640
Where? Where are they? Run!

1298
01:33:55,199 --> 01:33:56,600
-Run!
-Run!

1299
01:33:56,720 --> 01:33:58,800
-Run!
-Run!

1300
01:34:01,840 --> 01:34:02,880
Stop!

1301
01:34:03,199 --> 01:34:04,399
Don't come any closer!

1302
01:34:04,600 --> 01:34:07,079
Stop!

1303
01:34:07,239 --> 01:34:09,840
Don't come any closer or we'll jump!

1304
01:34:10,000 --> 01:34:13,119
-Don't come any closer!
-Stop!

1305
01:34:13,199 --> 01:34:14,399
-Don't come any closer!
-Don't!

1306
01:34:14,840 --> 01:34:15,880
Stop!

1307
01:34:15,960 --> 01:34:18,199
-What are you doing, Bedevi?
-Don't come near me!

1308
01:34:21,319 --> 01:34:22,840
What the hell are you doing, Bedevi?

1309
01:34:22,920 --> 01:34:24,199
Don't come any closer!

1310
01:34:24,840 --> 01:34:26,399
Come here, for God's sake!

1311
01:34:26,680 --> 01:34:28,239
Calm down. What is going on?

1312
01:34:28,319 --> 01:34:29,520
Are they protesting?

1313
01:34:29,600 --> 01:34:30,720
It's not a protest, Chief!

1314
01:34:31,119 --> 01:34:32,520
We are suffering!

1315
01:34:32,760 --> 01:34:34,760
For God's sake, come here!

1316
01:34:34,840 --> 01:34:36,520
What are you doing? Come here!

1317
01:34:36,720 --> 01:34:38,640
We can't do what you want us to do, Dad!

1318
01:34:39,159 --> 01:34:41,359
We don't want to end up like our moms.

1319
01:34:41,439 --> 01:34:44,439
We want to marry whoever we want!

1320
01:34:44,520 --> 01:34:47,920
The state can't choose
our husbands for us!

1321
01:34:48,680 --> 01:34:50,079
I'm still available, by the way.

1322
01:34:51,159 --> 01:34:52,199
Seyhan!

1323
01:34:52,319 --> 01:34:55,319
For heaven's sake, Seyhan! Come here!

1324
01:34:55,479 --> 01:34:57,439
Please don't do this, Seyhan. Come here.

1325
01:34:57,560 --> 01:35:00,119
I'm begging you. Come here, Seyhan!
Stop this nonsense.

1326
01:35:00,520 --> 01:35:02,560
I'll kill you if you jump, Diyar!
I swear to God!

1327
01:35:02,960 --> 01:35:06,039
I don't care about title deeds.
She is my daughter, after all.

1328
01:35:06,119 --> 01:35:07,319
You're absolutely right.

1329
01:35:07,880 --> 01:35:11,199
How can someone let their children die?

1330
01:35:13,600 --> 01:35:14,960
Shut up, you faggot!

1331
01:35:15,520 --> 01:35:18,159
-What the…
-We've made our decisions, Dad.

1332
01:35:18,359 --> 01:35:20,800
-If you don't approve, we'll jump!
-Wait!

1333
01:35:21,119 --> 01:35:23,239
What a dreadful bridge that is!

1334
01:35:23,319 --> 01:35:25,520
-We're still suffering because of it!
-Stop!

1335
01:35:26,279 --> 01:35:27,479
Stop.

1336
01:35:37,720 --> 01:35:39,039
It's all because of me.

1337
01:35:41,880 --> 01:35:43,560
I wrote the letter to the Ministry.

1338
01:35:44,000 --> 01:35:45,039
I am sorry.

1339
01:35:54,279 --> 01:35:58,640
God damn you, Teacher.
I don't have a woman because of you.

1340
01:35:59,279 --> 01:36:02,680
Guys! Enough with
the title deeds and all that.

1341
01:36:03,119 --> 01:36:06,680
Put an end to this situation
and let the lovers be reunited. Huh?

1342
01:36:07,479 --> 01:36:08,520
What do you say, Dad?

1343
01:36:08,600 --> 01:36:09,760
-What do you say, Dad?
-Right?

1344
01:36:09,840 --> 01:36:12,319
-Let the lovers come together!
-Yeah!

1345
01:36:12,600 --> 01:36:14,039
Right? Come on, Ado.

1346
01:36:14,920 --> 01:36:16,760
-Come on, Ado.
-Come on, Dad.

1347
01:36:17,079 --> 01:36:19,479
-Right?
-Right, Dad?

1348
01:36:21,199 --> 01:36:22,640
-Just say it's okay.
-Dad?

1349
01:36:22,840 --> 01:36:24,239
Yes, that's right.

1350
01:36:26,399 --> 01:36:28,399
-Come on, Ado.
-Come on already.

1351
01:36:28,720 --> 01:36:30,800
Okay. Come here.

1352
01:36:56,479 --> 01:36:57,680
Wait a minute!

1353
01:37:00,680 --> 01:37:02,960
Why doesn't anybody in this village
take me seriously?

1354
01:37:03,159 --> 01:37:04,560
I'm also protesting!

1355
01:37:05,359 --> 01:37:08,880
If you don't find a woman for me,
I swear I'll throw myself off here.

1356
01:37:09,239 --> 01:37:10,960
Huso! Hey!

1357
01:37:11,439 --> 01:37:12,880
I'm in a tough spot, Cevo.

1358
01:37:13,279 --> 01:37:14,399
Okay, all right.

1359
01:37:14,880 --> 01:37:16,600
Okay, we'll find someone for you.

1360
01:37:16,880 --> 01:37:19,079
And we will rebuild the bridge for you.

1361
01:37:20,880 --> 01:37:22,199
Well, I'm sold.

1362
01:37:22,479 --> 01:37:24,159
Goodness gracious!

1363
01:37:47,600 --> 01:37:50,199
"To the Republic of Turkey's
Ministry of Family,

1364
01:37:51,279 --> 01:37:55,520
thank you for answering my calls
and choosing us as your pilot area."

1365
01:37:56,840 --> 01:37:59,439
"However, this place isn't ready
to change just yet."

1366
01:38:00,640 --> 01:38:02,319
"Instead of making radical changes,

1367
01:38:02,479 --> 01:38:05,359
we made decisions
that could be implemented gradually."

1368
01:38:06,319 --> 01:38:08,399
"Removing borders and uniting people,

1369
01:38:08,800 --> 01:38:11,880
adjusting measures
to ensure people's happiness."

1370
01:38:13,199 --> 01:38:14,520
"That's what we did."

1371
01:38:15,000 --> 01:38:17,119
"Teacher Salih Ozturk."

1372
01:38:28,439 --> 01:38:29,439
Hello, Chief.

1373
01:38:30,159 --> 01:38:33,039
-Well, hello!
-Let's get straight to the point.

1374
01:38:35,199 --> 01:38:36,800
Can you please send this to Ankara?

1375
01:38:39,520 --> 01:38:42,319
-Is it another evil plan?
-No, it's not.

1376
01:38:43,920 --> 01:38:46,199
It seems that your bags are empty.

1377
01:38:48,840 --> 01:38:51,600
Unfortunately, they are.
Some faggot probably stole them.

1378
01:38:52,119 --> 01:38:56,279
-Yes. Some faggot.
-Yeah. That's what I said.

1379
01:38:56,640 --> 01:38:57,680
Take it easy.

1380
01:38:59,760 --> 01:39:00,760
Goodbye.

1381
01:39:03,279 --> 01:39:04,319
Faggot.

1382
01:39:10,359 --> 01:39:12,640
Look, everyone is gone.

1383
01:39:13,279 --> 01:39:15,560
Fucking peasants.

